</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="900">3. Setting up items for the Hood store</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Hood allows you to upload items and retrieve orders without an active store. You are required to have a store for some options, for example uploading item variations. You can <a href="https://www.hood.de/hood-shop-einrichten.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">book</a> a silver, gold or platinum store at Hood.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1000">3.1. Uploading item variations</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to book a store in order to upload item variations to Hood. Once you have booked a store on Hood, the items are integrated into Hood with category links. Set up the shop categories directly on <a href="https://www.hood.de/mein-shop.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hood</a>&nbsp;<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-external-link  "></i></span>. To do so, go to <strong>Mein Shop &gt; Shop-Einstellungen &gt; Kategorien</strong>. Then load the categories into plentymarkets. This allows you to select them in the listing.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Loading store categories for Hood:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Hood</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Store categories</strong> area, click on <strong>Update</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-undo  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The store categories are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Update the categories again if you added new store categories on Hood.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Hood does not allow HTML tags in the short description of "store item" listings</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>HTML tags are not taken into consideration when transmitting the short description for Hood listings of the type <strong>store item</strong>. This is because Hood does not support such HTML tags. The item’s <strong>Preview text</strong> is transferred from plentymarkets to Hood as the short description. This text is found by opening the item in the <strong>Item » Edit item</strong> menu and clicking on the <strong>Texts</strong> tab. Existing HTML tags are deleted and only plain text is transferred. <br>
HTML tags are permitted in the actual listing description.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1100">3.2. Displaying the stock status</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The status <strong>Hidden</strong> is assigned to Hood listings of the type <strong>Store item</strong> that do not have any stock. These listings are not ended.
This applies to Hood listings of the type <strong>Store item</strong> with the stock dependence <strong>limited (without reservation)</strong> and <strong>limited (with reservation)</strong>. These listings are not ended in plentymarkets either. Instead, they are displayed with the status <strong>Hidden</strong>. As soon as the item is back in stock in plentymarkets, the listing is reactivated on Hood during an automatic stock update.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1160">3.3. Linking your own properties</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to be able to use your own characteristics for the Hood market, the characteristics have to be activated for Hood in the <strong>Setup » Item » Characteristics</strong> menu. You can link up to 12 characteristics per item and use a maximum of 16 characters per name.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking your own properties:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Item » Characteristics</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the characteristic (<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-plus-square-o  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Display as Hood property</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The characteristic is included in the item’s list of characteristics on Hood.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Wildcard character in Layout template (Hood)</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If the <strong>Wildcard character in layout template (Hood)</strong> function is activated, the property is also displayed in the layout template of a listing, provided that the wildcard character is used.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="1200">4. Preparing listings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use listings to sell your items on the markets eBay, Hood and ricardo. The basic settings of listings are not related to any particular market. As such, you can use the same listing for one or more of these markets. The listings for all three markets are managed in the menu <strong>Setup » Listings</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="listings-definitions">5. Definitions</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title">What is a listing?</div>
<div class="content">
<div id="listing" class="dlist">
<dl>
<dt class="hdlist1">Listing</dt>
<dd>
<p>The listing contains basic settings that are independent of the platform, for example settings for stock dependence and listing contents. Here, you can also define the listing type. The listing types are <a href="#fixed-price">Fixed price</a>, <a href="#auction">Auction</a> or <a href="#shop-item">Shop item</a>.<br>
Each listing may be associated with multiple <a href="#market-listing">Market listings</a>.</p>
</dd>
</dl>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following listing types are available:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="#fixed-price">Fixed price</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#auction">Auction</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#shop-item">Store item</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title">What is a market listing?</div>
<div class="content">
<div id="market-listing" class="dlist">
<dl>
<dt class="hdlist1">Market listing</dt>
<dd>
<p>Offer on the marketplaces eBay, Hood, and ricardo. A market listing is always associated with exactly one <a href="#listing">Listing</a>. Use the market listing for example for carrying out settings specific to a single marketplace.</p>
</dd>
</dl>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title">What is a listing template?</div>
<div class="content">
<div id="listing-template" class="dlist">
<dl>
<dt class="hdlist1">Listing template</dt>
<dd>
<p>Template for listings. You can create a template using either the group function in the <strong>Listings » Edit listings » Tab: Group function</strong> menu or REST. A listing template contains settings for <a href="#listing">Listings</a>, <a href="#market-listing">Market listings</a> and actions for listings, as well as specific options for eBay, Hood, and ricardo. You can use the same template for any number of listings.</p>
</dd>
</dl>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1300">5.1. Carrying out the basic settings for listings</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to create listings in plentymarkets, you must carry out the following settings and have created your items. The settings in the <strong>Setup » Listings » Settings</strong> menu apply to all listings.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Other users are logged out automatically</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Whenever you carry out changes in the menu <strong>Setup » Listings » Settings</strong>, other users are logged out automatically and need to log in again. This ensures that the changes are applied to all user profiles.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Carrying out the basic settings for listings:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Listings » Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the desired settings. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#basic-settings-listings">Table 5</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.</p>
