<h2 id="2300">6. Creating listings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>plentymarkets provides you with multiple possibilities for creating listings:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>in the item overview</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>using batch processing</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>with an already existing listing</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>using the data format <a href="/en/data/export-import/data-formats/itemlistingmarketebay">ItemListingMarketEbay</a> to automatically create large quantities of items</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
You can only create listings for completely created items.
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Permanently keeping listings on Hood</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The maximum runtime for a Hood listing is 14 days. The following requirements have to be met in order to permanently keep listings on the platform:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>You have a Hood store (regardless of the booked store package).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The listing type is store item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>A store category is linked in the listing’s <strong>Market</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2400">6.1. Creating a new listing</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can create a new listing in the <strong>Item » Edit item</strong> menu by clicking on the <strong>New listing</strong> procedure in the line of an individual item.<br></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a new listing:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New listing</strong> in the line of an item.<br>
<strong><em>Or:</em></strong> Open an item and click on <strong>New listing</strong> in the toolbar.<br>
→ The <strong>New market listing</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#settings-new-market-listing">Table 11</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon "><i class="psicon-save"></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The listing is created and the listing overview opens.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
